					<p> Crop Biotech Update, 12 May 2006 |  The Horn Biotechnology Forum (HBF), founded in 2002, will hold a workshop on biotechnology in the Horn of Africa countries (Djibouti, Eritrea, Ethiopia, Somalia, and Sudan) on June 29, 2006 in Addis Ababa, Ethiopia. The &quot;Workshop on Present Status, Challenges and Future Opportunities&quot; aims to raise biotechnology awareness and promote understanding of the current status, challenges, and future opportunities of biotechnology applications for the region.</p>
