					<p> 20 July 2005 |  FAO - This document is a background paper to an e-forum conference hosted by the FAO Biotechnology Forum (June- July 2005), and considers the use of biotechnology tools in the characterisation and conservation of crop, forest, animal and fishery genetic resources in developing countries. It provides a brief overview of genetic resources for food and agriculture; detailed information regarding the current status of the genetic resources in the different food and agricultural sectors Crop, Forest, and Animal.</p>
